The finalized stable-identifier-drift rule (DESIGN §2). The seeded
.rackabel/state.toml records a previous pack of "Clip Renamer" at 1.1.0; the current
rackabel.toml renames the extension to "Clip Tool" and bumps to 1.2.0. validate emits
the §2 warning shape — the old identifier, the new one, the version it shipped in, and
the "existing setups may break" clause — as a non-fatal WARNING (exit 0). The
version-bump rule passes (1.2.0 > 1.1.0). Env is pinned inline (no Live → apiVersion
rule skips; isolated state root).

```
$ ABLETON_APP=/nonexistent-ableton-live.app RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home rackabel validate
[✓] manifest complete
[!] minimumApiVersion 1.0.0 — skipped (no Ableton Live found to compare against)
[✓] version 1.2.0 bumped (last packed 1.1.0)
[✓] CHANGELOG.md has an entry for 1.2.0
[!] native dependencies — none declared
warning: name `Clip Renamer` was renamed to `Clip Tool` (present in 1.1.0) — existing setups may break; keep the old name or provide a migration
1 warning

```
